## Entry Point
Read `CLAUDE.md` in the repo root FIRST. It is the navigation guide to the entire project.
Then read `wiki/00_SOVEREIGN/Agent_Knowledge_Handbook.md` for current state, known bugs, store inventory, and API map.

## Documentation Methodology
This project uses a **MemPalace + Karpathy** wiki methodology. All canonical knowledge lives in `wiki/`.
Do NOT trust documentation outside of `wiki/` and `CLAUDE.md` — scattered config files (`.kiro/`, old README files, session handoffs) may be outdated.

## Source of Truth Hierarchy
1. `CLAUDE.md` (root) — quick reference, deployment state, navigation
2. `wiki/00_SOVEREIGN/Agent_Knowledge_Handbook.md` — current stats, bugs, stores, API map, rules
3. `wiki/00_SOVEREIGN/Verdade_do_Produto.md` — honest product truth (no inflation)
4. `wiki/02_Arquitetura_Compass/` — technical architecture and API audit
5. `wiki/05_Infraestrutura/` — deployment runbooks

## Critical Rules
- DO NOT modify `apps/app-compass-v2/` or `apps/api-core-v2/` (frozen v2 production)
- DO NOT create new Zustand stores — consolidate existing ones
- DO NOT build gamification, social, or P3 features before core value works
- DO NOT skip `npm run type-check` before commits
- DO NOT trust `.kiro/specs/` — those specs are outdated and contradict current priorities
- Always use "Olcan Compass" (not "Compass" or "Olcan" alone) in first mention

